                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="91625" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 11:39:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do you mean by &quot;distribute&quot;? According to Spring&apos;s lifecycle definition, &lt;tt&gt;setApplicationContext(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; is called &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;afterPropertiesSet()&lt;/tt&gt;. This means, that by definition - that the &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContext&lt;/tt&gt; will be set &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;initialize()&lt;/tt&gt; is called and in turn &lt;tt&gt;createPersistentEntity(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; will be called the first time. As the &lt;tt&gt;PersistentEntity&lt;/tt&gt; instances will all be created by this method, we shouldn&apos;t see any instances without the &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationContext&lt;/tt&gt; being populated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re manually instantiating and using &lt;tt&gt;MongoMappingContext&lt;/tt&gt; make sure you call &lt;tt&gt;setApplicationContext(&#8230;)&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; &lt;tt&gt;initialize()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91636" author="ccox" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 13:59:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re absolutely right. &lt;tt&gt;AbstractMongoConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;mongoMappingContext&lt;/tt&gt; is calling &lt;tt&gt;initialize()&lt;/tt&gt; before it returns the bean. Still a bug, but much simpler to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91637" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 14:09:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The hint to JavaConfig was very helpful. It turns out, the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-569&quot; title=&quot;AbstractMongoConfiguration cannot be used on CloudFoundry&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAMONGO-569&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAMONGO-569&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has already solved this for 1.3 M1 already so that you shouldn&apos;t see this issue using the milestone anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I partially backported the fix and added a test case in the bugfix branch and forward ported the test case explicitly checking for the scenario you described into master in turn.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.3 M1 should have the fix, 1.2.2.BUILD-SNAPSHOT will have it in a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91639" author="ccox" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 14:31:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This takes care of &lt;a href=&quot;#DATAMONGO-718&quot;&gt;DATAMONGO-718&lt;/a&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
